PREREQUISITES

Android projects
- To build Android projects it's required that the Android SDK is setup on your system

REQUIREMENTS

- Create local.properties file to set the location of the Android SDK.  
  Example of local.properties file:
	sdk.dir=/path/to/Android/Sdk

  NOTE: The local.properties file should not be committed under the Version Control.

SOURCE PACKAGE CONTENT

- AndroidManifest.xml

 It's required that the project to be added into the build system had it's AndroidManifest.xml file with corresponding configuration.


INSTALL/UNINSTALL

Make sure adb is setup (comming with Android SDK, just make sure sdk/platform-tools are added to your PATH)
Make sure the app has no admin previledges to uninstall it via gradle
